OL,4,CWorkers watchdog launched to clamp down
OL,5,Con abuse
OL,6, The government has announced the
OL,7, creation of a new workers' watchdog to
OL,8, take over protecting the rights of UK
OL,9, workers.
OL,11,FThe new body will be responsible for
OL,12,Ftackling modern slavery, enforcing the
OL,13,Fminimum wage and protecting agency
OL,14,Fworkers.
OL,16,FCurrently these tasks are spread across
OL,17,Fthree different bodies.
OL,19,FThe new body aims to improve
OL,20,Fenforcement through better coordination
OL,21,Fand pooling intelligence.
